         <OBJECT_CONTRACT ITEM="1">
            <TITLE>
               <P>Procurement to support coordination of the supply chain for owner occupier retrofit at the local level</P>
            </TITLE>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="71314300"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SUPPLIES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>As part of a wider programme of work to improve the energy performance of owner occupier properties, as set out in the Clean Growth Strategy, and the Call for Evidence on “Building a market for energy efficiency”, BEIS is seeking to launch pilots to support coordination of the retrofit and renovation supply chain at a unitary authority level to deliver high quality retrofit projects. The funding awarded by BEIS would be used by up to three organisations in different areas over one and a half years to develop a sustainable model for driving retrofit in a local area, primarily amongst owner occupiers, in particular addressing the non-financial barriers to retrofit such as trust, hassle factor and lack of awareness.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">3000000</VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
